[2026-03-17T14:16:51Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019vXadUr32gvGUejzDquqSB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# Self-Evolution System Design\n     2ŌåÆ\n     3ŌåÆ## Overview\n     4ŌåÆ\n     5ŌåÆCloche's self-evolution system analyzes workflow run history and user feedback to\n     6ŌåÆautomatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows over\n     7ŌåÆtime. It is a daemon-side post-run pipeline that triggers after every workflow\n     8ŌåÆcompletion, applies changes directly to project files, and maintains a structured\n     9ŌåÆaudit trail.\n    10ŌåÆ\n    11ŌåÆThe system draws on the ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) framework for prompt\n    12ŌåÆevolution ŌĆö treating prompts as structured, itemized playbooks that accumulate\n    13ŌåÆlessons rather than monolithic documents that get rewritten.\n    14ŌåÆ\n    15ŌåÆ**Scope (this version):** Additive changes only. Prompt updates, new script\n    16ŌåÆsteps, new agent steps, new wiring. No step removal or mutation of existing step\n    17ŌåÆdefinitions.\n    18ŌåÆ\n    19ŌåÆ## Architecture\n    20ŌåÆ\n    21ŌåÆThe evolution system is a multi-stage pipeline with three specialized output\n    22ŌåÆbranches. The LLM handles classification, reflection, and content generation.\n    23ŌåÆDeterministic Go code handles structural manipulation (DSL editing, file I/O,\n    24ŌåÆaudit logging).\n    25ŌåÆ\n    26ŌåÆ```\n    27ŌåÆ                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n    28ŌåÆ                    Ōöé         Workflow Run Completes       Ōöé\n    29ŌåÆ                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n    30ŌåÆ                                   Ōöé\n    31ŌåÆ                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n    32ŌåÆ                    Ōöé           Collector                  Ōöé\n    33ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  Gathers: run results, history.log,  Ōöé\n    34ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  step outputs, knowledge base,       Ōöé\n    35ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  current prompts + workflow          Ōöé\n    36ŌåÆ                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n    37ŌåÆ                                   Ōöé\n    38ŌåÆ                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n    39ŌåÆ                    Ōöé         Classifier (LLM)            Ōöé\n    40ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  Categorizes run prompt:             Ōöé\n    41ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  bug | feedback | feature |          Ōöé\n    42ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  enhancement | chore                 Ōöé\n    43ŌåÆ                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n    44ŌåÆ                                   Ōöé\n    45ŌåÆ                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n    46ŌåÆ                    Ōöé         Reflector (LLM)              Ōöé\n    47ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  ACE-style: examines traces,         Ōöé\n    48ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  extracts structured lessons          Ōöé\n    49ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  (bullets with metadata)              Ōöé\n    50ŌåÆ                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n    51ŌåÆ                                   Ōöé\n    52ŌåÆ              ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n    53ŌåÆ              Ōöé                    Ōöé                     Ōöé\n    54ŌåÆ   ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n    55ŌåÆ   Ōöé  Prompt Curator    Ōöé Ōöé  Script Generator Ōöé Ōöé  DSL Mutator     Ōöé\n    56ŌåÆ   Ōöé  (LLM + dedup)     Ōöé Ōöé  (LLM)            Ōöé Ōöé  (Go code)       Ōöé\n    57ŌåÆ   Ōöé                    Ōöé Ōöé                    Ōöé Ōöé                   Ōöé\n    58ŌåÆ   Ōöé  Merges lessons    Ōöé Ōöé  Writes new        Ōöé Ōöé  Adds steps,     Ōöé\n    59ŌåÆ   Ōöé  into prompt files Ōöé Ōöé  checker/linter    Ōöé Ōöé  wiring, collects Ōöé\n    60ŌåÆ   Ōöé  as structured     Ōöé Ōöé  scripts           Ōöé Ōöé  to .cloche file  Ōöé\n    61ŌåÆ   Ōöé  bullets           Ōöé Ōöé                    Ōöé Ōöé                   Ōöé\n    62ŌåÆ   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n    63ŌåÆ            Ōöé                      Ōöé                      Ōöé\n    64ŌåÆ            ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n    65ŌåÆ                                   Ōöé\n    66ŌåÆ                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n    67ŌåÆ                    Ōöé         Audit Logger                 Ōöé\n    68ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  Records all changes + reasons        Ōöé\n    69ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  Updates knowledge base summary       Ōöé\n    70ŌåÆ                    Ōöé  Snapshots pre-change state           Ōöé\n    71ŌåÆ                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n    72ŌåÆ```\n    73ŌåÆ\n    74ŌåÆThe three branches fire independently based on lesson category. A single\n    75ŌåÆevolution pass may produce changes across multiple branches, or none at all.\n    76ŌåÆ\n    77ŌåÆ## Multi-Project Scoping\n    78ŌåÆ\n    79ŌåÆThe daemon supports multiple concurrent cloche instances across different\n    80ŌåÆprojects (and multiple runs within the same project). Every run record includes\n    81ŌåÆ`project_dir` ŌĆö the absolute path to the project directory where `cloche run`\n    82ŌåÆwas invoked.\n    83ŌåÆ\n    84ŌåÆAll evolution state is scoped by project_dir + workflow_name:\n    85ŌåÆ- SQLite queries filter by project_dir\n    86ŌåÆ- Knowledge bases live at `<project_dir>/.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.md`\n    87ŌåÆ- Evolution passes for different projects/workflows run independently\n    88ŌåÆ- One evolution pass at a time per project+workflow (mutex)\n    89ŌåÆ\n    90ŌåÆ## Data Collection\n    91ŌåÆ\n    92ŌåÆ### New Signals Captured Per Run\n    93ŌåÆ\n    94ŌåÆ| Signal               | Where captured                        | Notes                          |\n    95ŌåÆ|----------------------|---------------------------------------|--------------------------------|\n    96ŌåÆ| Assembled prompt     | Prompt adapter, before LLM invocation | Full text sent to the agent    |\n    97ŌåÆ| Agent stdout         | Prompt adapter, after agent returns   | Full LLM response              |\n    98ŌåÆ| Run prompt class     | Classifier LLM, post-run             | bug/feedback/feature/etc.      |\n    99ŌåÆ| Retry count per step | Prompt adapter attempt tracking       | Already in filesystem, add to SQLite |\n   100ŌåÆ| Project directory    | CLI sends to daemon via gRPC          | Currently implicit             |\n   101ŌåÆ\n   102ŌåÆ### Run Prompt Classification\n   103ŌåÆ\n   104ŌåÆThe Classifier examines each run's `--prompt` text and categorizes it:\n   105ŌåÆ\n   106ŌåÆ- **bug** ŌĆö fixing something broken; indicates a gap the system should reflect on\n   107ŌåÆ  for patterns in its approach to software development\n   108ŌåÆ- **feedback** ŌĆö code review style issues (DRY, SOLID, architecture); things\n   109ŌåÆ  caught in a typical review cycle that the system should watch its output for\n   110ŌåÆ- **feature** ŌĆö new functionality; normal work\n   111ŌåÆ- **enhancement** ŌĆö improving existing functionality\n   112ŌåÆ- **chore** ŌĆö maintenance; no evolution signal\n   113ŌåÆ\n   114ŌåÆBug and feedback runs are the primary evolution drivers. Features and\n   115ŌåÆenhancements provide background context but don't typically trigger changes.\n   116ŌåÆClassification happens via LLM inference on the prompt text ŌĆö no explicit\n   117ŌåÆ`--type` flag needed from the user.\n   118ŌåÆ\n   119ŌåÆ### SQLite Schema Additions\n   120ŌåÆ\n   121ŌåÆ```sql\n   122ŌåÆ-- Add project scoping to runs\n   123ŌåÆALTER TABLE runs ADD COLUMN project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '';\n   124ŌåÆ\n   125ŌåÆ-- Extend step_executions with captured data\n   126ŌåÆALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN prompt_text TEXT;\n   127ŌåÆALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN agent_output TEXT;\n   128ŌåÆALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN attempt_number INTEGER DEFAULT 1;\n   129ŌåÆ\n   130ŌåÆ-- Track evolution passes\n   131ŌåÆCREATE TABLE evolution_log (\n   132ŌåÆ    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   133ŌåÆ    project_dir TEXT NOT NULL,\n   134ŌåÆ    workflow_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n   135ŌåÆ    trigger_run_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n   136ŌåÆ    created_at DATETIME NOT NULL,\n   137ŌåÆ    classification TEXT,\n   138ŌåÆ    changes_json TEXT NOT NULL,\n   139ŌåÆ    knowledge_delta TEXT\n   140ŌåÆ);\n   141ŌåÆ```\n   142ŌåÆ\n   143ŌåÆ### On-Disk Evolution State\n   144ŌåÆ\n   145ŌåÆ```\n   146ŌåÆ.cloche/\n   147ŌåÆ  evolution/\n   148ŌåÆ    log.jsonl                   # append-only audit trail (one JSON object per line)\n   149ŌåÆ    knowledge/\n   150ŌåÆ      develop.md                # ACE-style knowledge base for 'develop' workflow\n   151ŌåÆ    snapshots/\n   152ŌåÆ      <timestamp>-<filename>    # pre-change backups for revert\n   153ŌåÆ```\n   154ŌåÆ\n   155ŌåÆ## Pipeline Stages\n   156ŌåÆ\n   157ŌåÆ### Stage 1: Collector\n   158ŌåÆ\n   159ŌåÆTriggers after every run completion. Gathers:\n   160ŌåÆ\n   161ŌåÆ1. All runs for this project+workflow since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n   162ŌåÆ   `evolution_log.trigger_run_id`)\n   163ŌåÆ2. The accumulated knowledge base (`knowledge/<workflow>.md`)\n   164ŌåÆ3. Current prompt files referenced by the workflow\n   165ŌåÆ4. The current `.cloche` workflow DSL file\n   166ŌåÆ5. Runs classified as \"bug\" or \"feedback\" carry more weight in analysis\n   167ŌåÆ\n   168ŌåÆIf there are no new runs since the last evolution, the pipeline short-circuits.\n   169ŌåÆ\n   170ŌåÆ### Stage 2: Classifier (LLM)\n   171ŌåÆ\n   172ŌåÆFor each unclassified run, the Classifier examines the run prompt and assigns a\n   173ŌåÆcategory. The classification is stored in the run record (SQLite) for use by the\n   174ŌåÆReflector and for future queries.\n   175ŌåÆ\n   176ŌåÆ### Stage 3: Reflector (LLM)\n   177ŌåÆ\n   178ŌåÆThe Reflector examines execution traces and extracts structured lessons. It\n   179ŌåÆreceives the collected run data (step results, failure logs, retry counts), the\n   180ŌåÆcurrent knowledge base, and the current prompts and workflow.\n   181ŌåÆ\n   182ŌåÆIt produces delta entries ŌĆö structured lessons:\n   183ŌåÆ\n   184ŌåÆ```json\n   185ŌåÆ{\n   186ŌåÆ  \"lessons\": [\n   187ŌåÆ    {\n   188ŌåÆ      \"id\": \"lesson-20260224-001\",\n   189ŌåÆ      \"category\": \"prompt_improvement\",\n   190ŌåÆ      \"target\": \"prompts/implement.md\",\n   191ŌåÆ      \"insight\": \"Agent consistently produces unsanitized HTML output in form handlers. 4 of last 6 bug-type runs involved XSS.\",\n   192ŌåÆ      \"suggested_action\": \"Add explicit rule: always sanitize user inputs with html.EscapeString() before template rendering\",\n   193ŌåÆ      \"evidence\": [\"run-abc\", \"run-def\", \"run-ghi\", \"run-jkl\"],\n   194ŌåÆ      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n   195ŌåÆ    },\n   196ŌåÆ    {\n   197ŌåÆ      \"id\": \"lesson-20260224-002\",\n   198ŌåÆ      \"category\": \"new_step\",\n   199ŌåÆ      \"step_type\": \"script\",\n   200ŌåÆ      \"insight\": \"No static security analysis in workflow. Security bugs only caught by user reports post-deployment.\",\n   201ŌåÆ      \"suggested_action\": \"Add gosec script step after test, wire failures to fix\",\n   202ŌåÆ      \"evidence\": [\"run-abc\", \"run-def\"],\n   203ŌåÆ      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n   204ŌåÆ    }\n   205ŌåÆ  ]\n   206ŌåÆ}\n   207ŌåÆ```\n   208ŌåÆ\n   209ŌåÆConfidence levels (high/medium/low) are based on evidence count and pattern\n   210ŌåÆconsistency. Only lessons meeting the configured minimum confidence proceed to\n   211ŌåÆthe executor branches.\n   212ŌåÆ\n   213ŌåÆ**Knowledge base deduplication:** After confidence filtering, the Reflector\n   214ŌåÆcross-references generated lesson IDs against the current knowledge base text.\n   215ŌåÆLessons whose ID already appears in the knowledge base are dropped, preventing\n   216ŌåÆthe same lessons from being re-surfaced across evolution cycles. The\n   217ŌåÆOrchestrator applies a second-layer ID filter as a guard, ensuring that even if\n   218ŌåÆthe Reflector misses a duplicate, previously applied lessons are not\n   219ŌåÆre-processed.\n   220ŌåÆ\n   221ŌåÆ### Stage 4: Executor Branches\n   222ŌåÆ\n   223ŌåÆBased on each lesson's `category`, it routes to one of three branches.\n   224ŌåÆ\n   225ŌåÆ#### Branch A: Prompt Curator (LLM + deterministic dedup)\n   226ŌåÆ\n   227ŌåÆHandles `prompt_improvement` lessons.\n   228ŌåÆ\n   229ŌåÆ- Receives the current prompt file content and the lesson\n   230ŌåÆ- **Content-change guard:** Before calling the LLM, the curator checks whether\n   231ŌåÆ  the lesson's key insight or suggested action is already present in the current\n   232ŌåÆ  prompt text (case-insensitive substring match). If the lesson is already\n   233ŌåÆ  incorporated, the curator returns immediately without calling the LLM and\n   234ŌåÆ  without rewriting the file. This prevents churn, snapshot bloat, and\n   235ŌåÆ  regression risk from unnecessary rewrites.\n   236ŌåÆ- ACE-style curation: merges the lesson into the prompt as a structured\n   237ŌåÆ  bullet/rule\n   238ŌåÆ- Deduplication: checks for semantic overlap with existing bullets; if a lesson\n   239ŌåÆ  refines an existing bullet, it updates in place rather than appending\n   240ŌåÆ- Code-fence stripping: LLM responses are cleaned of markdown code fences\n   241ŌåÆ  (` ``` `) before writing, extracting only the content between fences. This\n   242ŌåÆ  prevents meta-commentary or formatting artifacts from leaking into prompt files.\n   243ŌåÆ- Conversational response validation: after stripping code fences, the output is\n   244ŌåÆ  checked for conversational markers (e.g. \"I need write permission\", \"Here is\n   245ŌåÆ  the updated prompt:\", \"Could you grant access\"). If the LLM returned\n   246ŌåÆ  meta-conversation text instead of prompt content, the curator falls back to\n   247ŌåÆ  appending the lesson directly as a structured bullet rather than trusting the\n   248ŌåÆ  LLM output. This prevents prompt file corruption when the LLM produces\n   249ŌåÆ  interactive-style responses.\n   250ŌåÆ- **Post-write sanity check:** After writing the updated prompt to disk, the\n   251ŌåÆ  curator re-reads the file and validates it: the content must be non-empty,\n   252ŌåÆ  must not start with conversational phrases, and must contain at least one\n   253ŌåÆ  markdown heading (`#`). If the sanity check fails, the curator restores the\n   254ŌåÆ  file from the pre-change snapshot and returns a `prompt_update_rollback`\n   255ŌåÆ  change entry instead of `prompt_update`. The snapshot is preserved as\n   256ŌåÆ  evidence.\n   257ŌåÆ- Output: the modified prompt file content, written to disk\n   258ŌåÆ\n   259ŌåÆ#### Branch B: Script Generator (LLM)\n   260ŌåÆ\n   261ŌåÆHandles `new_step` lessons where step_type is \"script\" or \"agent\".\n   262ŌåÆ\n   263ŌåÆ- Receives the lesson describing what check or analysis is needed\n   264ŌåÆ- Generates a script file (shell, Python, etc.) implementing the check, or a\n   265ŌåÆ  prompt file for agent steps\n   266ŌåÆ- Script/prompt is written to the project directory (e.g.,\n   267ŌåÆ  `scripts/security-scan.sh` or `prompts/review.md`)\n   268ŌåÆ- Output: the file path and content\n   269ŌåÆ\n   270ŌåÆ#### Branch C: DSL Mutator (deterministic Go code)\n   271ŌåÆ\n   272ŌåÆHandles structural workflow changes. Receives structured proposals and applies\n   273ŌåÆthem to the `.cloche` workflow file. Four operations:\n   274ŌåÆ\n   275ŌåÆ**Add Step Definition:**\n   276ŌåÆ```json\n   277ŌåÆ{\n   278ŌåÆ  \"op\": \"add_step\",\n   279ŌåÆ  \"name\": \"security-scan\",\n   280ŌåÆ  \"type\": \"script\",\n   281ŌåÆ  \"config\": {\n   282ŌåÆ    \"run\": \"gosec ./...\",\n   283ŌåÆ    \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n   284ŌåÆ  }\n   285ŌåÆ}\n   286ŌåÆ```\n   287ŌåÆ\n   288ŌåÆParses the workflow file, inserts the step definition, serializes back.\n   289ŌåÆ\n   290ŌåÆ**Add Wiring:**\n   291ŌåÆ```json\n   292ŌåÆ{\n   293ŌåÆ  \"op\": \"add_wire\",\n   294ŌåÆ  \"wires\": [\n   295ŌåÆ    {\"from\": \"test\", \"result\": \"success\", \"to\": \"security-scan\"},\n   296ŌåÆ    {\"from\": \"security-scan\", \"result\": \"fail\", \"to\": \"fix\"}\n   297ŌåÆ  ]\n   298ŌåÆ}\n   299ŌåÆ```\n   300ŌåÆ\n   301ŌåÆAppends wires to the wiring section.\n   302ŌåÆ\n   303ŌåÆ**Rewire Result:**\n   304ŌåÆ```json\n   305ŌåÆ{\n   306ŌåÆ  \"op\": \"rewire_result\",\n   307ŌåÆ  \"from\": \"test\",\n   308ŌåÆ  \"result\": \"success\",\n   309ŌåÆ  \"old_to\": \"done\",\n   310ŌåÆ  \"new_to\": \"security-scan\"\n   311ŌåÆ}\n   312ŌåÆ```\n   313ŌåÆ\n   314ŌåÆChanges the target of an existing wire. Used by the orchestrator when inserting\n   315ŌåÆa new step into the graph: it finds a wire pointing to `done`, rewires it to\n   316ŌåÆthe new step, then wires the new step's results to terminals. This splices the\n   317ŌåÆnew step into the existing flow rather than creating a disconnected node.\n   318ŌåÆ\n   319ŌåÆ**Update Collect:**\n   320ŌåÆ```json\n   321ŌåÆ{\n   322ŌåÆ  \"op\": \"update_collect\",\n   323ŌåÆ  \"collect_target\": \"done\",\n   324ŌåÆ  \"add_conditions\": [\n   325ŌåÆ    {\"step\": \"security-scan\", \"result\": \"success\"}\n   326ŌåÆ  ]\n   327ŌåÆ}\n   328ŌåÆ```\n   329ŌåÆ\n   330ŌåÆFinds the matching `collect` clause and adds the new condition.\n   331ŌåÆ\n   332ŌåÆ**Validation gate:** After any mutation, the mutator calls\n   333ŌåÆ`domain.Workflow.Validate()` on the result. If validation fails, the mutation is\n   334ŌåÆrejected, the original file is preserved, and the failure is logged.\n   335ŌåÆ\n   336ŌåÆ**DSL Serializer:** The mutator requires a round-trip-preserving serializer ŌĆö\n   337ŌåÆparse into an AST that retains comments and whitespace, modify the AST, serialize\n   338ŌåÆback. This preserves user formatting and comments.\n   339ŌåÆ\n   340ŌåÆBranches B and C often fire together ŌĆö a new script step needs both the script\n   341ŌåÆfile (B) and the DSL wiring (C).\n   342ŌåÆ\n   343ŌåÆ### Stage 5: Audit Logger\n   344ŌåÆ\n   345ŌåÆAfter all changes are applied:\n   346ŌåÆ\n   347ŌåÆ1. **Snapshot** ŌĆö copies pre-change versions of all modified files to\n   348ŌåÆ   `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n   349ŌåÆ2. **Restore** ŌĆö restores a file from a named snapshot (used by the Curator\n   350ŌåÆ   to roll back corrupted writes)\n   351ŌåÆ3. **Log** ŌĆö appends a JSONL entry to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` and inserts\n   352ŌåÆ   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n   353ŌåÆ4. **Knowledge base update** ŌĆö merges the Reflector's lessons into\n   354ŌåÆ   `knowledge/<workflow>.jsonl` with ID-based deduplication and optional\n   355ŌåÆ   pruning via `MaxPromptBullets`\n   356ŌåÆ\n   357ŌåÆ## Knowledge Base Structure\n   358ŌåÆ\n   359ŌåÆThe knowledge base is a JSONL file ŌĆö one JSON object per line, each\n   360ŌåÆrepresenting a `Lesson`. Lessons are keyed by `id` for deduplication: if a\n   361ŌåÆlesson with the same ID already exists, it is updated in place rather than\n   362ŌåÆappended. When `MaxPromptBullets` is configured and the total number of\n   363ŌåÆlessons exceeds that limit, the oldest entries are pruned to stay within\n   364ŌåÆbounds.\n   365ŌåÆ\n   366ŌåÆ```jsonl\n   367ŌåÆ{\"id\":\"P001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Always sanitize user inputs with html.EscapeString() before template rendering\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add sanitization rule to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n   368ŌåÆ{\"id\":\"W001\",\"category\":\"new_step\",\"step_type\":\"script\",\"insight\":\"Added gosec security scan step\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add gosec step to workflow\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n   369ŌåÆ{\"id\":\"F001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Test timeout failures correlate with database connection setup\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add retry guidance to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-ghi\",\"run-jkl\"],\"confidence\":\"medium\"}\n   370ŌåÆ```\n   371ŌåÆ\n   372ŌåÆThe structured JSONL format enables reliable deduplication by lesson ID and\n   373ŌåÆprogrammatic querying. Lessons that are superseded by newer insights with the\n   374ŌåÆsame ID are replaced automatically.\n   375ŌåÆ\n   376ŌåÆ## Trigger Logic\n   377ŌåÆ\n   378ŌåÆ### When Evolution Runs\n   379ŌåÆ\n   380ŌåÆThe pipeline triggers in the daemon after every workflow run completes (success\n   381ŌåÆor failure). Smart throttling prevents waste:\n   382ŌåÆ\n   383ŌåÆ- **Debounce:** If runs complete in rapid succession (parallel runs on the same\n   384ŌåÆ  project), wait a configurable period (default 30s) after the last completion\n   385ŌåÆ  before triggering. This batches multiple runs into one analysis pass.\n   386ŌåÆ- **Mutex:** If an evolution pass is already in progress for this\n   387ŌåÆ  project+workflow, skip. The next run completion will pick up the slack.\n   388ŌåÆ- **No-op detection:** If the Reflector finds nothing actionable (clean feature\n   389ŌåÆ  runs, no patterns), the pipeline logs \"no changes\" and exits without firing\n   390ŌåÆ  the executor branches.\n   391ŌåÆ\n   392ŌåÆ### History Window\n   393ŌåÆ\n   394ŌåÆThe Collector gathers all runs since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n   395ŌåÆ`evolution_log.trigger_run_id`). The knowledge base provides the long-term\n   396ŌåÆmemory ŌĆö once raw runs are analyzed, their lessons persist in the knowledge base\n   397ŌåÆeven as the raw data ages out. This gives the system both recency (raw run data)\n   398ŌåÆand continuity (accumulated knowledge).\n   399ŌåÆ\n   400ŌåÆ## Protocol Changes\n   401ŌåÆ\n   402ŌåÆ### gRPC (CLI to Daemon)\n   403ŌåÆ\n   404ŌåÆ```protobuf\n   405ŌåÆmessage RunRequest {\n   406ŌåÆ  string workflow = 1;\n   407ŌåÆ  string prompt = 2;\n   408ŌåÆ  string project_dir = 3;   // NEW\n   409ŌåÆ}\n   410ŌåÆ```\n   411ŌåÆ\n   412ŌåÆ### Status Protocol (Agent to Daemon)\n   413ŌåÆ\n   414ŌåÆ```protobuf\n   415ŌåÆmessage StepStarted {\n   416ŌåÆ  string step_name = 1;\n   417ŌåÆ  string prompt_text = 2;    // NEW: assembled prompt\n   418ŌåÆ}\n   419ŌåÆ\n   420ŌåÆmessage StepCompleted {\n   421ŌåÆ  string step_name = 1;\n   422ŌåÆ  string result = 2;\n   423ŌåÆ  string agent_output = 3;   // NEW: LLM response\n   424ŌåÆ  int32 attempt_number = 4;  // NEW\n   425ŌåÆ}\n   426ŌåÆ```\n   427ŌåÆ\n   428ŌåÆ### Prompt Adapter Changes\n   429ŌåÆ\n   430ŌåÆThe prompt adapter captures the assembled prompt text before invoking the agent\n   431ŌåÆand the agent's stdout after it returns. Both are forwarded to the daemon via\n   432ŌåÆthe status protocol. No changes to prompt assembly logic ŌĆö the evolution system\n   433ŌåÆmodifies prompt files on disk, and the existing `file()` mechanism picks up\n   434ŌåÆchanges on the next run.\n   435ŌåÆ\n   436ŌåÆ## Configuration\n   437ŌåÆ\n   438ŌåÆPer-project in `.cloche/config`:\n   439ŌåÆ\n   440ŌåÆ```toml\n   441ŌåÆ[evolution]\n   442ŌåÆenabled = true                # master switch\n   443ŌåÆdebounce_seconds = 30         # wait after last run before analyzing\n   444ŌåÆmin_confidence = \"medium\"     # minimum lesson confidence to act on\n   445ŌåÆmax_prompt_bullets = 50       # cap on knowledge bullets per prompt\n   446ŌåÆ```\n   447ŌåÆ\n   448ŌåÆEvolution is enabled by default. Users can disable it per-project for static\n   449ŌåÆworkflows.\n   450ŌåÆ\n   451ŌåÆ## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n   452ŌåÆ\n   453ŌåÆ- **Step removal/mutation** ŌĆö modifying or removing existing step definitions\n   454ŌåÆ  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n   455ŌåÆ- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** ŌĆö automated revert from snapshots\n   456ŌåÆ- **Helpfulness tracking** ŌĆö automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n   457ŌåÆ  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n   458ŌåÆ- **Cross-project learning** ŌĆö sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n   459ŌåÆ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b01b4e7c-06dd-40f1-863a-61952eecce5b","uuid":"701b1456-ca1b-4f8c-92a6-2a3d145c6ef7","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:16:16.829Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md","content":"# Self-Evolution System Design\n\n## Overview\n\nCloche's self-evolution system analyzes workflow run history and user feedback to\nautomatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows over\ntime. It is a daemon-side post-run pipeline that triggers after every workflow\ncompletion, applies changes directly to project files, and maintains a structured\naudit trail.\n\nThe system draws on the ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) framework for prompt\nevolution ŌĆö treating prompts as structured, itemized playbooks that accumulate\nlessons rather than monolithic documents that get rewritten.\n\n**Scope (this version):** Additive changes only. Prompt updates, new script\nsteps, new agent steps, new wiring. No step removal or mutation of existing step\ndefinitions.\n\n## Architecture\n\nThe evolution system is a multi-stage pipeline with three specialized output\nbranches. The LLM handles classification, reflection, and content generation.\nDeterministic Go code handles structural manipulation (DSL editing, file I/O,\naudit logging).\n\n```\n                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n                    Ōöé         Workflow Run Completes       Ōöé\n                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n                                   Ōöé\n                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n                    Ōöé           Collector                  Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  Gathers: run results, history.log,  Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  step outputs, knowledge base,       Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  current prompts + workflow          Ōöé\n                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n                                   Ōöé\n                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n                    Ōöé         Classifier (LLM)            Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  Categorizes run prompt:             Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  bug | feedback | feature |          Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  enhancement | chore                 Ōöé\n                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n                                   Ōöé\n                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n                    Ōöé         Reflector (LLM)              Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  ACE-style: examines traces,         Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  extracts structured lessons          Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  (bullets with metadata)              Ōöé\n                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n                                   Ōöé\n              ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n              Ōöé                    Ōöé                     Ōöé\n   ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n   Ōöé  Prompt Curator    Ōöé Ōöé  Script Generator Ōöé Ōöé  DSL Mutator     Ōöé\n   Ōöé  (LLM + dedup)     Ōöé Ōöé  (LLM)            Ōöé Ōöé  (Go code)       Ōöé\n   Ōöé                    Ōöé Ōöé                    Ōöé Ōöé                   Ōöé\n   Ōöé  Merges lessons    Ōöé Ōöé  Writes new        Ōöé Ōöé  Adds steps,     Ōöé\n   Ōöé  into prompt files Ōöé Ōöé  checker/linter    Ōöé Ōöé  wiring, collects Ōöé\n   Ōöé  as structured     Ōöé Ōöé  scripts           Ōöé Ōöé  to .cloche file  Ōöé\n   Ōöé  bullets           Ōöé Ōöé                    Ōöé Ōöé                   Ōöé\n   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n            Ōöé                      Ōöé                      Ōöé\n            ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n                                   Ōöé\n                    ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n                    Ōöé         Audit Logger                 Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  Records all changes + reasons        Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  Updates knowledge base summary       Ōöé\n                    Ōöé  Snapshots pre-change state           Ōöé\n                    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n```\n\nThe three branches fire independently based on lesson category. A single\nevolution pass may produce changes across multiple branches, or none at all.\n\n## Multi-Project Scoping\n\nThe daemon supports multiple concurrent cloche instances across different\nprojects (and multiple runs within the same project). Every run record includes\n`project_dir` ŌĆö the absolute path to the project directory where `cloche run`\nwas invoked.\n\nAll evolution state is scoped by project_dir + workflow_name:\n- SQLite queries filter by project_dir\n- Knowledge bases live at `<project_dir>/.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.md`\n- Evolution passes for different projects/workflows run independently\n- One evolution pass at a time per project+workflow (mutex)\n\n## Data Collection\n\n### New Signals Captured Per Run\n\n| Signal               | Where captured                        | Notes                          |\n|----------------------|---------------------------------------|--------------------------------|\n| Assembled prompt     | Prompt adapter, before LLM invocation | Full text sent to the agent    |\n| Agent stdout         | Prompt adapter, after agent returns   | Full LLM response              |\n| Run prompt class     | Classifier LLM, post-run             | bug/feedback/feature/etc.      |\n| Retry count per step | Prompt adapter attempt tracking       | Already in filesystem, add to SQLite |\n| Project directory    | CLI sends to daemon via gRPC          | Currently implicit             |\n\n### Run Prompt Classification\n\nThe Classifier examines each run's `--prompt` text and categorizes it:\n\n- **bug** ŌĆö fixing something broken; indicates a gap the system should reflect on\n  for patterns in its approach to software development\n- **feedback** ŌĆö code review style issues (DRY, SOLID, architecture); things\n  caught in a typical review cycle that the system should watch its output for\n- **feature** ŌĆö new functionality; normal work\n- **enhancement** ŌĆö improving existing functionality\n- **chore** ŌĆö maintenance; no evolution signal\n\nBug and feedback runs are the primary evolution drivers. Features and\nenhancements provide background context but don't typically trigger changes.\nClassification happens via LLM inference on the prompt text ŌĆö no explicit\n`--type` flag needed from the user.\n\n### SQLite Schema Additions\n\n```sql\n-- Add project scoping to runs\nALTER TABLE runs ADD COLUMN project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '';\n\n-- Extend step_executions with captured data\nALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN prompt_text TEXT;\nALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN agent_output TEXT;\nALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN attempt_number INTEGER DEFAULT 1;\n\n-- Track evolution passes\nCREATE TABLE evolution_log (\n    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    project_dir TEXT NOT NULL,\n    workflow_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n    trigger_run_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n    created_at DATETIME NOT NULL,\n    classification TEXT,\n    changes_json TEXT NOT NULL,\n    knowledge_delta TEXT\n);\n```\n\n### On-Disk Evolution State\n\n```\n.cloche/\n  evolution/\n    log.jsonl                   # append-only audit trail (one JSON object per line)\n    knowledge/\n      develop.md                # ACE-style knowledge base for 'develop' workflow\n    snapshots/\n      <timestamp>-<filename>    # pre-change backups for revert\n```\n\n## Pipeline Stages\n\n### Stage 1: Collector\n\nTriggers after every run completion. Gathers:\n\n1. All runs for this project+workflow since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n   `evolution_log.trigger_run_id`)\n2. The accumulated knowledge base (`knowledge/<workflow>.md`)\n3. Current prompt files referenced by the workflow\n4. The current `.cloche` workflow DSL file\n5. Runs classified as \"bug\" or \"feedback\" carry more weight in analysis\n\nIf there are no new runs since the last evolution, the pipeline short-circuits.\n\n### Stage 2: Classifier (LLM)\n\nFor each unclassified run, the Classifier examines the run prompt and assigns a\ncategory. The classification is stored in the run record (SQLite) for use by the\nReflector and for future queries.\n\n### Stage 3: Reflector (LLM)\n\nThe Reflector examines execution traces and extracts structured lessons. It\nreceives the collected run data (step results, failure logs, retry counts), the\ncurrent knowledge base, and the current prompts and workflow.\n\nIt produces delta entries ŌĆö structured lessons:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"lessons\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"lesson-20260224-001\",\n      \"category\": \"prompt_improvement\",\n      \"target\": \"prompts/implement.md\",\n      \"insight\": \"Agent consistently produces unsanitized HTML output in form handlers. 4 of last 6 bug-type runs involved XSS.\",\n      \"suggested_action\": \"Add explicit rule: always sanitize user inputs with html.EscapeString() before template rendering\",\n      \"evidence\": [\"run-abc\", \"run-def\", \"run-ghi\", \"run-jkl\"],\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"lesson-20260224-002\",\n      \"category\": \"new_step\",\n      \"step_type\": \"script\",\n      \"insight\": \"No static security analysis in workflow. Security bugs only caught by user reports post-deployment.\",\n      \"suggested_action\": \"Add gosec script step after test, wire failures to fix\",\n      \"evidence\": [\"run-abc\", \"run-def\"],\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nConfidence levels (high/medium/low) are based on evidence count and pattern\nconsistency. Only lessons meeting the configured minimum confidence proceed to\nthe executor branches.\n\n**Knowledge base deduplication:** After confidence filtering, the Reflector\ncross-references generated lesson IDs against the current knowledge base text.\nLessons whose ID already appears in the knowledge base are dropped, preventing\nthe same lessons from being re-surfaced across evolution cycles. The\nOrchestrator applies a second-layer ID filter as a guard, ensuring that even if\nthe Reflector misses a duplicate, previously applied lessons are not\nre-processed.\n\n### Stage 4: Executor Branches\n\nBased on each lesson's `category`, it routes to one of three branches.\n\n#### Branch A: Prompt Curator (LLM + deterministic dedup)\n\nHandles `prompt_improvement` lessons.\n\n- Receives the current prompt file content and the lesson\n- **Content-change guard:** Before calling the LLM, the curator checks whether\n  the lesson's key insight or suggested action is already present in the current\n  prompt text (case-insensitive substring match). If the lesson is already\n  incorporated, the curator returns immediately without calling the LLM and\n  without rewriting the file. This prevents churn, snapshot bloat, and\n  regression risk from unnecessary rewrites.\n- ACE-style curation: merges the lesson into the prompt as a structured\n  bullet/rule\n- Deduplication: checks for semantic overlap with existing bullets; if a lesson\n  refines an existing bullet, it updates in place rather than appending\n- Code-fence stripping: LLM responses are cleaned of markdown code fences\n  (` ``` `) before writing, extracting only the content between fences. This\n  prevents meta-commentary or formatting artifacts from leaking into prompt files.\n- Conversational response validation: after stripping code fences, the output is\n  checked for conversational markers (e.g. \"I need write permission\", \"Here is\n  the updated prompt:\", \"Could you grant access\"). If the LLM returned\n  meta-conversation text instead of prompt content, the curator falls back to\n  appending the lesson directly as a structured bullet rather than trusting the\n  LLM output. This prevents prompt file corruption when the LLM produces\n  interactive-style responses.\n- **Post-write sanity check:** After writing the updated prompt to disk, the\n  curator re-reads the file and validates it: the content must be non-empty,\n  must not start with conversational phrases, and must contain at least one\n  markdown heading (`#`). If the sanity check fails, the curator restores the\n  file from the pre-change snapshot and returns a `prompt_update_rollback`\n  change entry instead of `prompt_update`. The snapshot is preserved as\n  evidence.\n- Output: the modified prompt file content, written to disk\n\n#### Branch B: Script Generator (LLM)\n\nHandles `new_step` lessons where step_type is \"script\" or \"agent\".\n\n- Receives the lesson describing what check or analysis is needed\n- Generates a script file (shell, Python, etc.) implementing the check, or a\n  prompt file for agent steps\n- Script/prompt is written to the project directory (e.g.,\n  `scripts/security-scan.sh` or `prompts/review.md`)\n- Output: the file path and content\n\n#### Branch C: DSL Mutator (deterministic Go code)\n\nHandles structural workflow changes. Receives structured proposals and applies\nthem to the `.cloche` workflow file. Four operations:\n\n**Add Step Definition:**\n```json\n{\n  \"op\": \"add_step\",\n  \"name\": \"security-scan\",\n  \"type\": \"script\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"run\": \"gosec ./...\",\n    \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nParses the workflow file, inserts the step definition, serializes back.\n\n**Add Wiring:**\n```json\n{\n  \"op\": \"add_wire\",\n  \"wires\": [\n    {\"from\": \"test\", \"result\": \"success\", \"to\": \"security-scan\"},\n    {\"from\": \"security-scan\", \"result\": \"fail\", \"to\": \"fix\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nAppends wires to the wiring section.\n\n**Rewire Result:**\n```json\n{\n  \"op\": \"rewire_result\",\n  \"from\": \"test\",\n  \"result\": \"success\",\n  \"old_to\": \"done\",\n  \"new_to\": \"security-scan\"\n}\n```\n\nChanges the target of an existing wire. Used by the orchestrator when inserting\na new step into the graph: it finds a wire pointing to `done`, rewires it to\nthe new step, then wires the new step's results to terminals. This splices the\nnew step into the existing flow rather than creating a disconnected node.\n\n**Update Collect:**\n```json\n{\n  \"op\": \"update_collect\",\n  \"collect_target\": \"done\",\n  \"add_conditions\": [\n    {\"step\": \"security-scan\", \"result\": \"success\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nFinds the matching `collect` clause and adds the new condition.\n\n**Validation gate:** After any mutation, the mutator calls\n`domain.Workflow.Validate()` on the result. If validation fails, the mutation is\nrejected, the original file is preserved, and the failure is logged.\n\n**DSL Serializer:** The mutator requires a round-trip-preserving serializer ŌĆö\nparse into an AST that retains comments and whitespace, modify the AST, serialize\nback. This preserves user formatting and comments.\n\nBranches B and C often fire together ŌĆö a new script step needs both the script\nfile (B) and the DSL wiring (C).\n\n### Stage 5: Audit Logger\n\nAfter all changes are applied:\n\n1. **Snapshot** ŌĆö copies pre-change versions of all modified files to\n   `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n2. **Restore** ŌĆö restores a file from a named snapshot (used by the Curator\n   to roll back corrupted writes)\n3. **Log** ŌĆö appends a JSONL entry to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` and inserts\n   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n4. **Knowledge base update** ŌĆö merges the Reflector's lessons into\n   `knowledge/<workflow>.jsonl` with ID-based deduplication and optional\n   pruning via `MaxPromptBullets`\n\n## Knowledge Base Structure\n\nThe knowledge base is a JSONL file ŌĆö one JSON object per line, each\nrepresenting a `Lesson`. Lessons are keyed by `id` for deduplication: if a\nlesson with the same ID already exists, it is updated in place rather than\nappended. When `MaxPromptBullets` is configured and the total number of\nlessons exceeds that limit, the oldest entries are pruned to stay within\nbounds.\n\n```jsonl\n{\"id\":\"P001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Always sanitize user inputs with html.EscapeString() before template rendering\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add sanitization rule to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n{\"id\":\"W001\",\"category\":\"new_step\",\"step_type\":\"script\",\"insight\":\"Added gosec security scan step\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add gosec step to workflow\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n{\"id\":\"F001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Test timeout failures correlate with database connection setup\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add retry guidance to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-ghi\",\"run-jkl\"],\"confidence\":\"medium\"}\n```\n\nThe structured JSONL format enables reliable deduplication by lesson ID and\nprogrammatic querying. Lessons that are superseded by newer insights with the\nsame ID are replaced automatically.\n\n## Trigger Logic\n\n### When Evolution Runs\n\nThe pipeline triggers in the daemon after every workflow run completes (success\nor failure). Smart throttling prevents waste:\n\n- **Debounce:** If runs complete in rapid succession (parallel runs on the same\n  project), wait a configurable period (default 30s) after the last completion\n  before triggering. This batches multiple runs into one analysis pass.\n- **Mutex:** If an evolution pass is already in progress for this\n  project+workflow, skip. The next run completion will pick up the slack.\n- **No-op detection:** If the Reflector finds nothing actionable (clean feature\n  runs, no patterns), the pipeline logs \"no changes\" and exits without firing\n  the executor branches.\n\n### History Window\n\nThe Collector gathers all runs since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n`evolution_log.trigger_run_id`). The knowledge base provides the long-term\nmemory ŌĆö once raw runs are analyzed, their lessons persist in the knowledge base\neven as the raw data ages out. This gives the system both recency (raw run data)\nand continuity (accumulated knowledge).\n\n## Protocol Changes\n\n### gRPC (CLI to Daemon)\n\n```protobuf\nmessage RunRequest {\n  string workflow = 1;\n  string prompt = 2;\n  string project_dir = 3;   // NEW\n}\n```\n\n### Status Protocol (Agent to Daemon)\n\n```protobuf\nmessage StepStarted {\n  string step_name = 1;\n  string prompt_text = 2;    // NEW: assembled prompt\n}\n\nmessage StepCompleted {\n  string step_name = 1;\n  string result = 2;\n  string agent_output = 3;   // NEW: LLM response\n  int32 attempt_number = 4;  // NEW\n}\n```\n\n### Prompt Adapter Changes\n\nThe prompt adapter captures the assembled prompt text before invoking the agent\nand the agent's stdout after it returns. Both are forwarded to the daemon via\nthe status protocol. No changes to prompt assembly logic ŌĆö the evolution system\nmodifies prompt files on disk, and the existing `file()` mechanism picks up\nchanges on the next run.\n\n## Configuration\n\nPer-project in `.cloche/config`:\n\n```toml\n[evolution]\nenabled = true                # master switch\ndebounce_seconds = 30         # wait after last run before analyzing\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"     # minimum lesson confidence to act on\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50       # cap on knowledge bullets per prompt\n```\n\nEvolution is enabled by default. Users can disable it per-project for static\nworkflows.\n\n## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n\n- **Step removal/mutation** ŌĆö modifying or removing existing step definitions\n  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** ŌĆö automated revert from snapshots\n- **Helpfulness tracking** ŌĆö automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n- **Cross-project learning** ŌĆö sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n","numLines":459,"startLine":1,"totalLines":459}}}
